 rolling down a hill? Yes, that is also a real thing that this company real=
ly did.But was the company =E2=80=9Can =E2=80=98intricate=E2=80=99 or =E2=
=80=98massive fraud=E2=80=99=E2=80=9D? No, no, what are you talking about, =
not a fraud at all.My point was that startups, in their early stages, somet=
imes say things that aren't quite true in order to encourage a shared sense=
 of belief by employees and investors, and that if this works it can sort o=
f be bootstrapped into reality. If Nikola=E2=80=99s founder lied about its =
trucks early on, in order to raise funding to make those trucks real, then,=
 as I put it, =E2=80=9Cthat's not a =E2=80=98massive fraud,=E2=80=99 that=
=E2=80=99s just, like, startups, man.=E2=80=9DThis is a better defense for=
=C2=A0Nikola=C2=A0=E2=80=94 a continuing company that is trying to make tru=
cks with all that money =E2=80=94=C2=A0than it is for that=C2=A0founder, th=
ough. If he lied to investors, that=E2=80=99s not great, even if later ever=
ything more or less comes true.  Anyway:Nikola Corp. founder and former cha=
irman Trevor Milton has been charged by prosecutors with making false state=
ments to investors in the electric-vehicle startup.Milton, who stepped down=
 from the company in September, is in federal custody after voluntarily sur=
rendering. He=E2=80=99s charged with misleading investors from November 201=
9 until about September 2020 with the development of Nikola=E2=80=99s produ=
cts and technology, according to an indictment unsealed Thursday by federal=
 prosecutors in N.Y. The Securities and Exchange Commission also filed a co=
mplaint against him.Here are the SEC and Justice Department announcements. =
Here=E2=80=99s the indictment, which suggests that Milton was =E2=80=A6=C2=
=A0a good meme-stock CEO?For example, on or about March 2, 2020, which was =
the day before Nikola publicly announced that it would combine with VectoIQ=
, MILTON wrote in an email to a member of the board of directors of Nikola,=
 that we =E2=80=9Cneed to make sure we are getting=C2=A0retail investors on=
 our side. That is what prevents the stock short selling. This is super imp=
ortant to me.=E2=80=9DAccordingly, TREVOR MILTON, the defendant, appeared f=
or numerous interviews on podcasts and on television, and in print and onli=
ne media, beginning immediately following the announcement of Nikola=E2=80=
=99s going public combination with VectoIQ.=C2=A0Also, like everyone else,=
=C2=A0the grand jury can=E2=80=99t resist that=C2=A0truck rolling down the =
hill:In or about 2017, a representative of a large multinational corporatio=
n approached Nikola and asked to use the Nikola One in a commercial celebra=
ting innovation. The concept for the video included a shot of the Nikola On=
e coming to a stop in front of a stop sign. In order to accomplish this fea=
t with a vehicle that could not drive, the Nikola One was towed to the top =
of hill, at which point the =E2=80=9Cdriver=E2=80=9D released the brakes, a=
nd the truck rolled down the hill until being brought to a stop in front of=
 the stop sign. For additional takes, the truck was towed to the top of the=
 hill and rolled down the hill twice more. Additionally, the Nikola One=E2=
=80=99s door, which had been constructed using minivan parts, had to be tap=
ed up during the shoot to prevent it from falling off. Moreover, because th=
e Nikola One had not been tested and was not safe (and indeed could not ope=
rate), certain precautions were taken before towing the vehicle to the comm=
ercial shoot. In particular, the turbine, which was designed to run on natu=
ral gas, and batteries were entirely removed from the vehicle to mitigate r=
isk of fire, explosion, or damage. =E2=80=A6Following the commercial shoot,=
 TREVOR MILTON, the defendant, directed a Nikola employee to make a condens=
ed video of the Nikola One truck moving using raw footage from the shoot. =
=E2=80=A6=C2=A0In the video, the Nikola One appears to be driving down a ro=
ad with no incline. In other words, the Nikola One appears to be driving on=
 its own power, notwithstanding that the Nikola One could not do so and has=
 never done so.
